title: Secret Service agent who saved Reagan after shooting dies
text: > Top News Secret Service agent who saved Reagan after shooting dies FILE - In this March 30, 1981 file photo, U.S. President Ronald Reagan is shown being shoved into the President's limousine by secret service agents after being shot outside a Washington hotel. Secret service agent Jerry Parr, in raincoat to the right of Reagan, who pushed Reagan into the limousine, was credited with saving President Ronald Reaganâ€™s life on the day he was shot, has died. He was 85. (AP Photo/Ron Edmonds)
